      <h1 class='title'>Matters to which court is to have regard in exercising its powers under this Part - general</h1>
    </div>
    <div class='grand-committee-report-sitting' id='content'>
      
      <cite class='section'>HL Deb 17 May 2004 vol 661 c297GC</cite>
      <a class='permalink column-permalink' id='column_297gc' title='Col. 297GC &mdash; HL Deb 17 May 2004 vol 661 c297GC' name='column_297gc' href='#column_297gc' rel='bookmark'>297GC</a>
      <p class='procedural' id='S5LV0661P0-03853'>
        <a class='permalink' href='#S5LV0661P0_20040517_GCR_464' title='Link to this contribution' rel='bookmark'>&sect;</a>
        4 If an application is made for an order under this Part, the court, in deciding&#x2014;
        <ol>
        <li>(a) whether to exercise its powers under this Part, and</li>
        <li>(b) if so, in what way,</li></ol>
        must have regard to all the circumstances of the case, giving first consideration to the welfare while under 18 of any child of the family who has not reached 18.
      </p>
      <ol class='xoxo'>
        
